# Documentation Language

## Canonical Language
- All project documentation, including rules, plans, roadmaps, and RFCs, MUST be written in English.
- If a non-English version exists, an English version MUST be the canonical source of truth and kept in sync.

## Scope
- Applies to `.cursor/rules/`, `docs/`, RFCs/ADRs, product/tech plans, and any Markdown-based documentation within the repository.
- Complements `.cursor/rules/code-language.mdc` (identifiers) and `.cursor/rules/code-comments.mdc` (comments).

## Authoring Guidance
- Use clear, simple English.
- Prefer structured sections: Summary, Context, Goals/Non-goals, Decisions, Open Questions.

## Enforcement
- PRs introducing documentation MUST include English content.
- Reviewers MUST block merges when English is missing or incomplete for canonical docs.

## Migration
- Existing plans or docs in other languages MUST be translated into English. The English version becomes canonical; other languages are optional mirrors.